@startuml
title Failover Health Criteria (Decision Model)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam maxMessageSize 140

start
:Collect inputs;
note right
Inputs (from /decision):
- primary_reachable?
- replica_healthy?
- no_split_brain?
- failure_duration >= N?
- wal_lag_bytes <= threshold?
- caught_up? (receive_lsn == replay_lsn)
end note

if (primary_reachable?) then (yes)
  :BLOCKED;
  note right
  Not a failover scenario.
  Continue monitoring.
  end note
  stop
else (no)
  :primary unreachable;
endif

if (failure stable for N seconds?) then (no)
  :BLOCKED (risk=MEDIUM);
  note right
  Wait until failure is stable
  to avoid flapping.
  end note
  stop
endif

if (replica healthy?) then (no)
  :BLOCKED (risk=HIGH);
  stop
endif

if (no split brain?) then (no)
  :BLOCKED (risk=HIGH);
  note right
  If both are reachable and both
  claim primary -> block automation.
  end note
  stop
endif

if (wal lag ok AND caught up?) then (no)
  :BLOCKED (risk=HIGH);
  note right
  Prevent data loss:
  standby not fully replayed.
  end note
  stop
endif

:SAFE TO FAILOVER (risk=LOW);
note right
Controller actions:
1) promote standby (pg_ctl promote)
2) switch active region (/admin/switch)
end note
stop

@enduml

